## Summary

Using the Poincaré inequality and the representation formula, we show that on the 3-dimensional real Heisenberg group, $\mathbb{H}^{1}$, there exists a constant $C>0$ such that:

\[\left|\nabla e^{t\,\Delta}f\right|(g)\leqslant Ce^{t\,\Delta}\big{(}|\nabla f| \big{)}(g),\quad\forall g\in\mathbb{H}^{1},\ t>0,\ f\in C_{o}^{\infty}\big{(} \mathbb{H}^{1}\big{)}.\]

This result answers affirmatively the open question in [B.K. Driver, T. Melcher, Hypoelliptic heat kernel inequalities on the Heisenberg group, J. Funct. Anal. 221 (2005) 340-365]. Moreover, the main result of [B.K. Driver, T. Melcher, Hypoelliptic heat kernel inequalities on the Heisenberg group, J. Funct. Anal. 221 (2005) 340-365] can be considered as an immediate consequence of the above inequality. 2006 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.

