## 2 Reminder on the Poincaré inequality and the representation formula

There are many works on the Poincaré inequality and the integral representation of a function in terms of its gradient, see for example [19,22] and their references. In particular, there exists a constant $C > 0$ such that for any $f \in C_0^\infty(\mathbb{H}^1)$, any $g \in \mathbb{H}^1$, and any $r > 0$, we have:Here is the translation:

\[\int\limits_{B(g,r)}\big{|}f(g^{\prime})-f_{r}(g)\big{|}\,dg^{\prime}\leqslant Cr \int\limits_{B(g,r)}\big{|}\nabla f(g^{\prime})\big{|}\,dg^{\prime}, \tag{2.1}\]

\[|f(g^{\prime})-f_{r}(g)|\leqslant C\int\limits_{B(g,r)}|\nabla f(g_{s})|\frac{d(g^{\prime},g_{s})}{|B(g^{\prime},d(g^{\prime},g_{s}))|}\, dg_{s},\quad\forall g^{\prime}\in B(g,r), \tag{2.2}\]

